article.headline: Niagara 77, Loyola, Md. 57
article.story: LEWISTON, N.Y. -- Tyrone Lewis scored 21 points to lead four players in double figures as Niagara defeated Loyola (Md.) 77-57 on Sunday. Bilal Benn had 13 points and 10 rebounds for his sixth double-double of the season and the Purple Eagles (6-3, 2-0 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference) were 13-for-30 from beyond the arc (43.3 percent). Niagara led 38-30 at halftime and increased the lead to 47-37 before going on a 12-2 run for a 59-39 advantage with 9:49 to play. Demetrious Williamson hit consecutive 3-pointers and Kashief Edwards scored four straight points in the run. They finished with 11 points each. Niagara outscored Loyola 26-4 on fastbreak points. Jamal Barney led the Greyhounds (4-4, 0-2) with 18 points and 11 rebounds and J'hared Hall added 10 points. The Purple Eagles held Loyola leading scorer Brett Harvey, who entered averaging 15.1 points, to five points.
